        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the Navier–Stokes and scalar transport equations; observed order of accuracy within 10% of theoretical second-order convergence; all NPARC Alliance benchmark problems passed."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS verification on the rotating-frame Navier–Stokes equations confirms observed spatial order 1.94 (theoretical 2.0, deviation 3%). Temporal scheme verified to first-order for pseudo-transient stepping. All five NPARC Alliance CFD V&V benchmark cases passed within specified tolerances. Code verification evidence is complete and documented in VV-Report-NCV-2024."
    },
