        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes (coarse 2.1 M, medium 5.8 M, fine 14.2 M cells); Grid Convergence Index (GCI) < 2% for hemolysis index QoI; y+ < 1 on all wetted surfaces."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted at the 5 L/min / 3000 RPM operating point. GCI for hemolysis index: 1.3% (medium-to-fine transition). GCI for pressure rise: 0.8%. y+ ≤ 0.9 maintained on all blood-contacting surfaces with 15-layer prismatic inflation. Discretization error is well-controlled and exceeds Gradation 4 threshold; Gradation 5 achieved."
    },
