        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile, outlet static pressure, fluid temperature, hematocrit) measured and reported with calibrated instrumentation; measurement uncertainty propagated into simulation boundary conditions; all five operating points replicated in simulation."
      },
      "rationale": "PIV inlet velocity profiles measured with ±1.5% uncertainty (Dantec FlowSense 4M). Outlet pressure set by calibrated transducer (±0.3 mmHg). Blood analogue (glycerin–water, hematocrit-matched viscosity) characterised rheologically prior to each run. All five operating points reproduced in CFD with boundary conditions set to measured mean values ± 1σ. Test condition fidelity exceeds Gradation 3 threshold."
    },
    {
