        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Primary QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint; secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) are mechanistically linked to red blood cell damage; all QoIs are defined in the regulatory submission protocol."
      },
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — normalised index of hemolysis (NIH, g/100 L) — is the direct clinical regulatory metric for blood pump hemolysis per FDA guidance (2017). Secondary QoIs (volume-averaged shear stress, scalar stress exposure time) are mechanistically linked to the power-law hemolysis model and are directly measurable in the bench test. QoI relevance is fully established at Gradation 4."
