        "description": "Turbulence model selection justified by literature benchmark; hemolysis power-law model coefficients validated against published red blood cell lysis data; model form uncertainty estimated via comparison of k-ω SST and RSM results."
      },
      "rationale": "Turbulence: k-ω SST selected based on superior performance in rotating-passage benchmark studies (Hariharan et al. 2011, Passerini et al. 2013). Model form uncertainty quantified by comparing k-ω SST vs. Reynolds Stress Model predictions: NIH difference 4.2% (within acceptance band). Hemolysis power-law (Giersiepen–Wurzinger) coefficients validated against 18 published RBC lysis datasets (R² = 0.91). Model form evidence complete at Gradation 4."
